Subject: Sidney Lau romanisation 
To: Kennedy
Content:
  Wenzhounese romanisation Sidney Lau is a system of romanisation for Cantonese, developed by Sidney Lau for teaching Cantonese. It was developed for use in Cantonese radio, and is essentially an adaptation of the Meyer-Wempe romanisation. Seven tones are indicated using superscripted numbers.
